HEADWORD: Handy-dandy
<hw>Hand"y-dan`dy</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧nd"⟦ycr⟧*d⟦acr⟧n`d⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A child's play, one child guessing in which closed
hand the other holds some small object, winning the object if right and
forfeiting an equivalent if wrong; hence, forfeit.</def> <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

